<subSubSection id="C315650CF430FF8AFF30FDD24429FD23" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB03687F430FF8AFF30FDD24429FD23" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97BEA95F430FF8AFF30FDD2415EFD00" bold="true" box="[197,332,620,644]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is from the Latin word 
<emphasis id="B97BEA95F430FF8AFCDCFDD24376FD00" box="[809,868,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">solea</emphasis>
, which means the shoe of an animal, and postfix 
<emphasis id="B97BEA95F430FF8AFA7BFDD340ADFD2C" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">– alis</emphasis>
, which means like. This refers to the horseshoe-like juxta of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
